                                        <strong>Pro Tip:</strong> Regular daily records help you understand what conditions work best for your plants, allowing you to replicate success and troubleshoot problems!
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <!-- Question 2 -->
                        <div class="accordion-item faq-item">
                            <h3 class="accordion-header">
                                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#dr2">
                                    <i class="bi bi-question-circle-fill text-warning me-2"></i>
                                    What is VPD and why does it matter?
                                </button>
                            </h3>
                            <div id="dr2" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#dataAccordion">
                                <div class="accordion-body">
                                    <p><strong>VPD (Vapor Pressure Deficit)</strong> is the difference between the moisture in the air and how much moisture the air can hold when saturated.</p>
                                    <p><strong>Why it matters:</strong></p>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li>Influences plant transpiration rates</li>
                                        <li>Affects nutrient uptake efficiency</li>
                                        <li>Impacts plant stress levels</li>
                                        <li>Helps optimize growing conditions</li>
                                    </ul>
                                    <p><strong>Ideal VPD ranges:</strong></p>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li>Seedlings/Clones: 0.4-0.8 kPa</li>
                                        <li>Vegetative: 0.8-1.2 kPa</li>
                                        <li>Flowering: 1.0-1.5 kPa</li>
                                    </ul>
                                    <p class="mb-0">GardenHub automatically calculates VPD from your temperature and humidity readings!</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

